ol.li:
Here is an example NAD to create a Layer 2 trunk-mode virtio interface with
                    static IPAM:apiVersion: "k8s.cni.cncf.io/v1"
kind: NetworkAttachmentDefinition
metadata:
  name: vswitch
spec:
  config: '{
    "cniVersion":"0.4.0",
    "name": "vswitch",
    "type": "jcnr",
    "args": {
      "instanceName": "vswitch",
      "instanceType": "virtual-switch",
      "vlanIdList":"201, 202, 203"
    },
    "ipam": {
         "type": "static",
         "capabilities":{"ips":true},
         "addresses":[
           {
             "address":"10.2.1.1/24",
             "gateway":"10.2.1.253"
           },
           {
             "address":"2001::10.2.1.1/120",
             "gateway":"2001::10.2.1.253"
           }
         ]
    },
    "kubeConfig":"/etc/kubernetes/kubelet.conf"
  }'The NAD defines the VLAN IDs for the
                        virtual-switch instance to which the pod's trunk interface
                    will be attached.
